Package: RWisecondorX
Title: An 'R' Port of 'WisecondorX' for Copy Number Analysis using 'Duckhts'
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: 
    c(
        person(given = "Sounkou Mahamane", family = "Toure", email = "sounkoutoure@gmail.com", comment = c( ORCID = "0009-0001-5914-6798" ),
    role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person(given = "WisecondorX Authors", role = "ctb", comment = "Authors of the original WisecondorX tool implemented in Python")
    )
Description: An 'R' implementation of the 'WisecondorX' workflow for copy number analysis of cell-free DNA sequencing data, built on the 'duckhts' extension for 'DuckDB'.
            Reads BAM/CRAM files via 'duckhts' and replicates the 'WisecondorX' convert, newref, and predict stages in R and SQL.
            Optional conformance testing against the official 'wisecondorx' bioconda package is available via 'condathis' and 'reticulate'; no Python installation is required at runtime.
Imports: Rduckhts(>= 1.1.6-0.0.2), DBI, duckdb, utils
Suggests: tinytest, condathis, reticulate
Additional_repositories: https://rgenomicsetl.r-universe.dev
Config/WisecondorX/bioconda-package: wisecondorx
License: GPL (>= 3)
Encoding: UTF-8
